description:
Clment Philibert Lo Delibes (21 February 1836  16 January 1891) was a French composer of the Romantic era (18151910), who specialised in ballets, operas, and other works for the stage. His most notable works include the ballets Copplia (1870) and Sylvia (1876), as well as the operas Le roi l'a dit (1873) and Lakm (1883).

Lo Delibes
